          <title>LeBron James beats buzzer with tip to lift Lakers past Pacers and keep record streak alive</title>
          <description><![CDATA[INDIANAPOLIS (AP) — LeBron James had a buzzer-beating tip-in to cap a 10-point fourth quarter, Luka Doncic scored 34 points and the Los Angeles Lakers beat the Indiana Pacers 120-119 on Wednesday night. James extended his NBA-record streak of 10 or more points to 1,283 games — barely.]]></description>
